en.name: Messa
en.tip: A place with a heavier business feel.
en.tip_dish: All dishes are done to perfection, especially the sea bass.
en.tip_seating: No preffered seating we recommend.
en.tip_parking: There is paid parking nearby.

en.name: Joya
en.tip: A Casual italian place, quiet and simple.
en.tip_dish: Oder the Sophia Loren, beautiful and yummy.
en.tip_seating: As for a corner table inside.
en.tip_parking: There's a free parking lot in the evenings, at the school nearby or a paid lot.

en.name: Herbert Samuel
en.tip: This is a place to come at sunset.
en.tip_dish: Try the Balkan shrimp salad.
en.tip_seating: Ask to sit at the top level, near the windows.
en.tip_parking: There's valet parking if you call them up.

en.name: Raphael
en.tip: A place for fine dining with a great view.
en.tip_dish: Order the lamb chops.
en.tip_seating: If you're coming with friends, order the round table.
en.tip_parking: There is enough parking at the London Square paid lot nearby.

en.name: Onami
en.tip: A high end Japanese restaurant.
en.tip_dish: Go for the sashimi specials.
en.tip_seating: At the tables near the windows, not the inner space.
en.tip_parking: There is nearby paid parking.

en.name: Tapeo
en.tip: A well established tapas place, for happy hour with good friends.
en.tip_dish: Order a sangria, then another...
en.tip_seating: Seating on the bar is fun here.
en.tip_parking: There's paid parking nearby.

en.name: Turkiz
en.tip: An ocean view restaurant with a great fish and sea food menu. Ask for the cigar box at the end.
en.tip_dish: Oder the Tortellin or Grouper Kebab.
en.tip_seating: Ask for the round table.
en.tip_parking: There is parking along the street or paid parking earby.

en.name: Boya
en.tip: A very decent place at the Tel Aviv port, great for tourists.
en.tip_dish: You won't go wrong with the fish here.
en.tip_seating: The tables near the windows are obviousely more fun.
en.tip_parking: Park at the port's paid lots.

en.name: Dallal
en.tip: It used to be an old house built in the Arabic tradition, today you'll find there a home for those of you who appreciate fine dining.
en.tip_dish: Get the salmon scalop, a rare find in Tel Aviv.
en.tip_seating: To sit, ask for a booth.
en.tip_parking: There are nearby paid parking lots on HaMered street.

en.name: Suzanna
en.tip: A place for local food with a busy vibe.
en.tip_dish: This is a place to try local stuffed veggies.
en.tip_seating: No specific table is any better than others.
en.tip_parking: There's nearby paid parking lots on HaMered street.

en.name: Social Club
en.tip: A place with a sexy and busy vibe.
en.tip_dish: There's an exciting cocktail menu.
en.tip_seating: If you're looking for a nice bar restaurant, this is it.
en.tip_parking: PArk at the Beit Zion paid parking nearby.

en.name: Makom Shel Basar
en.tip: A great place for good meat.
en.tip_dish: We dont really need to tell you what to order...
en.tip_seating: Ask for a seat near the windows.
en.tip_parking: There's a small paid parking lot nearby. A taxi is a better idea.

en.name: Vicki Cristina
en.tip: A fun tapas bar in a good area.
en.tip_dish: Try the mini hamburguesas or crispy calamares, but honestly it's all just fun.
en.tip_seating: If you come with a large party, the large round bar table is good.
en.tip_parking: There is paid parking at the old station complex.

en.name: Abraxas North
en.tip: One of the best restaurants in Tel Aviv, yet surprisingly loud.
en.tip_dish: Order the rumpsteak burger or any of the chef takes on local dishes like the aubergene.
en.tip_seating: If you're with friends, ask to sit on the sofas on the second level.
en.tip_parking: Better take a taxi, hardly any parking around.

en.name: Zepra
en.tip: Daring Asian cuisine.
en.tip_dish: Don't miss out on the shrimp popcorn.
en.tip_seating: Even the bar is great.
en.tip_parking: Street parking should be fine.

en.name: Nanuchka
en.tip: Authentic georgian food.
en.tip_dish: Order the hinikali and lamb kebabs.
en.tip_seating: The bar comes alive at night.
en.tip_parking: There's scarce parking nearby.

en.name: Port Said
en.tip: A place for friends and street food with a twist, very unique Tel Aviv vibe, no reservations.
en.tip_dish: Try the chicken sandwich.
en.tip_seating: If you find a table, sell it for a profit.
en.tip_parking: There's paid parking with an entrance from Ehad Haam st.

en.name: Kalamata
en.tip: A great place to come if you're at the old Jaffa city.
en.tip_dish: The starters are more interesting than what the main courses have to offer.
en.tip_seating: As for a table near the windows - a must.
en.tip_parking: Use the parking at the old Jaffa mount.

en.name: Hotel Montefiore
en.tip: A classic fine dining establishment.
en.tip_dish: Have the Vietnamese crispy chicken.
en.tip_seating: No preffered seating recommendation.
en.tip_parking: You'll find paid parking nearby. But there's valet as well.

en.name: Elba
en.tip: Romantic, open glass wall, facing busy Tel Aviv.
en.tip_dish: Order the mangold and meiri cheese burekkas.
en.tip_seating: Sit by the windows.
en.tip_parking: There's a nearby paid parking lot.

en.name: CafÃ© Europa
en.tip: A patio restraurant in Rothschild, with great food.
en.tip_dish: Have the tortellini.
en.tip_seating: Take a seat inside, not near the entrance.
en.tip_parking: There's paid parking on Montefiore st. nearby.

en.name: Hatzer Goldman
en.tip: A great seaside location.
en.tip_dish: Have the Syrian kebab.
en.tip_seating: Choose a place near the windows.
en.tip_parking: There is paid parking nearby.

en.name: Shila
en.tip: Dim & loud at it's very best in Tel Aviv.
en.tip_dish: Order the bacon wrapped tenderloin.
en.tip_seating: Ask for a place in the space to the right of the entrance.
en.tip_parking: There is a valet service at the entrance.

en.name: Tapas 1 ha'am
en.tip: Great Spanish vibe.
en.tip_dish: The specials come out with a ring of the bell. Don't miss out.
en.tip_seating: If you come with friends, ask for the high tables at the left.
en.tip_parking: There is valet parking at the door.

en.name: Sola
en.tip: A quiant and romatic place in Jaffa.
en.tip_dish: The lazagne won't let you down.
en.tip_seating: Ask for the corner table next to the book shelves at the end.
en.tip_parking: Street parking should be fine.

en.name: Taizu
en.tip: A ×•niquely asian restaurant, in true Tel Aviv style.
en.tip_dish: Don't forget to order the house bread.
en.tip_seating: Seating inside is more impressive than the balcony.
en.tip_parking: Park at the Levinstein parking lot, special rates for the restaurant.

en.name: Juz & Luz
en.tip: A quality asain place.
en.tip_dish: The ramen will do you good.
en.tip_seating: Ask for a table not near the entrance.
en.tip_parking: There is paid parking on Allenby st.

en.name: Toto
en.tip: Quality fine dining near the TLV Museum.
en.tip_dish: Order the ox tail tortellini.
en.tip_seating: As to be seated away from the entrance.
en.tip_parking: There is nearby paid parking at the museum.

en.name: Mel & Michelle
en.tip: A genuinely romantic place for a good dinner.
en.tip_dish: It's rare to find Parisian Gniocco in Tel Aviv, try it.
en.tip_seating: Ask for the first table at right of the door.
en.tip_parking: Better take a cab.

en.name: Mitbach Laila
en.tip: Bar feel, great food.
en.tip_dish: Order the ox tail gniocci.
en.tip_seating: Notice that the tables here are bar tables.
en.tip_parking: Better take a taxi.

en.name: Yassou
en.tip: A fun greek restaurant bar with a great view of the Tel Aviv promenade.
en.tip_dish: We recommend the calamari or the shrimp.
en.tip_seating: Have the drinks outside, and the food inside.
en.tip_parking: Park at the paid lot next to the entrance.

en.name: Flee Market
en.tip: A fun place at the edge of the flee market in Jaffa.
en.tip_dish: Order the Jaffa kebabs.
en.tip_seating: The bar is cool as well.
en.tip_parking: Nearby street parking should be fine.

en.name: Kitchen Market
en.tip: Seafood restaurant overlooking the new port of Tel Aviv.
en.tip_dish: The Gazpacho is delightful.
en.tip_seating: Ask for the corner table overlooking the harbour.
en.tip_parking: Use the port toursit parking.

en.name: Alma
en.tip: Lounge restaurant located in a boutique hotel on Rothschild.
en.tip_dish: Order the ravioli with chicken mousse.
en.tip_seating: There are no tables here, it's more of a lounge.
en.tip_parking: Use the valet parking arranged at the nearby Tapas retaurant.

en.name: HaShulchan
en.tip: Chef restaurant on the Rothschild avenue.
en.tip_dish: The menu changes quite a bit, but order the most creative meat dish you see.
en.tip_seating: Ask for a table near the windows to the avenue.
en.tip_parking: Use the Maze st. pad parking lot.

en.name: Popina
en.tip: A fine dining combination of different cooking styles.
en.tip_dish: The dishes are small here, but you'll just want more.
en.tip_seating: The bar is nice and intimate.
en.tip_parking: Use the Africa-Israel building parking lot.

en.name: Cocina Tamar
en.tip: A place for good food, with a simple honest mood.
en.tip_dish: Go for the meat dishes.
en.tip_seating: Ask for a place inside, not near the entrance.
en.tip_parking: You'll find parking along the street or paid parking nearby.

en.name: Coffee Bar
en.tip: Well established restaurant, causal and classy.
en.tip_dish: Order the prawns with artichoke hearts.
en.tip_seating: No special seating recommendations.
en.tip_parking: There's paid parking nearby.

en.name: Cheder Ochel
en.tip: Here you'll find Kibutz food with a quality twist. Fun with friends or family.
en.tip_dish: Order the fish sinyeh.
en.tip_seating: The inner space is nicer than the balcony.
en.tip_parking: Use the museum parking lot.

en.name: Vong
en.tip: An intimate asian place.
en.tip_dish: It has the best Pho in town.
en.tip_seating: Seat in the patio if it's not too cold..
en.tip_parking: You'll find some paid parking at Ehad Haam st.

en.name: Pronto
en.tip: One of the best Italian places in town.
en.tip_dish: Order the lamb papardelle.
en.tip_seating: Ask for a table near the windows.
en.tip_parking: There is a nearby paid parking lot.

en.name: Yakimono
en.tip: A classy Japanese retaurant at the heart of Rothschild.
en.tip_dish: Have the Suimono soup, a rare delight.
en.tip_seating: Sit at the bar, or order a table next to the windows.
en.tip_parking: There's paid parking behind the restaurant.

en.name: Mul-Yam
en.tip: The eldest of the sea food restaurants, open view to the wooden deck of the Tel Aviv harbour.
en.tip_dish: If there's a lobster today, go for it.
en.tip_seating: The seats nearer to the deck are nicer.
en.tip_parking: Restaurant has its own parking inside the port. Call in advance.

en.name: Sardinia
en.tip: An intimate Italian restaurant, at the top of old Jaffa, not only for tourists.
en.tip_dish: Order the linguine Bottarga, a Sicilian special.
en.tip_seating: Sit outside if possible.
en.tip_parking: Use the old Jaffa parking lot.

en.name: Adora
en.tip: An Israeli chef kitchen with little pretence.
en.tip_dish: Order the Flamenquin pork.
en.tip_seating: No preffered seating recommendations.
en.tip_parking: Take a taxi.

en.name: David veYosef
en.tip: Chef restaurant with a lounge and a dominant bar.
en.tip_dish: Order the duck spring roll.
en.tip_seating: Sit at the bar inside.
en.tip_parking: Use the valet or paid parking nearby.

en.name: Bertie
en.tip: An Eastern Mediterranean restaurant with a local vibe.
en.tip_dish: Order the renowned veal cheek.
en.tip_seating: Ask to sit by the windows.
en.tip_parking: This is a hard to find parking. Nearest is Dizingoff centre paid lot.

en.name: Hanoi
en.tip: Asian food with an Asian setting.
en.tip_dish: Finally, truly good ramen soup.
en.tip_seating: Sit at the bar facing the street.
en.tip_parking: There is paid parking nearby.

en.name: Belini
en.tip: Solid italian, with a cultured setting.
en.tip_seating: We have no seating recommendations.
en.tip_parking: There is nearby paid parking on HaMered street.

en.name: Aria
en.tip: A fine dining setting in a renovated boutique building. First floor serves as a classy bar.
en.tip_dish: Order the Coquies st Jaques.
en.tip_seating: Ask for the table by the stairs, next to the window.
en.tip_parking: There is paid parking nearby.

en.name: Bistro Eden
en.tip: The feel of a boutique hotel.
en.tip_seating: We recommend sitting by the windows.
en.tip_parking: Take a taxi, there's little parking around.

en.name: Alora
en.tip: An open balcony italian restaurant on Rothschild blvd.
en.tip_seating: On nice days, it's a great place to eat on the balcony.
en.tip_parking: There is paid parking next to the restaurant.

en.name: NG
en.tip: A great place for meat and friends.
en.tip_dish: Go for the porterhouse steak.
en.tip_seating: The inside hall, by the windows.
en.tip_parking: Small paid parking lot nearby.

en.name: Blue Sky
en.tip: A hotel-top fine dining restaurant.
en.tip_dish: Order the Emotions of the Sea.
en.tip_seating: Have a few ocktails outside before eating.
en.tip_parking: Use the hotel parking.

en.name: Pastel
en.tip: One of several TLV Museum restaurant.
en.tip_dish: Order the Bavette steak.
en.tip_seating: The inner hall is beautiful.
en.tip_parking: Use the museum parking lot.

en.name: Rothschild
en.tip: A quiet boutique hotal restaurant.
en.tip_dish: Order the Triggerfish, if it's on that day.
en.tip_seating: Ask not to sit on the right side lobby area.
en.tip_parking: Park at the Maze st. parking lot.

en.name: Container
en.tip: A restaurant on the old port of Jaffa with a hipster twist.
en.tip_dish: Order some of the fresh fish and sea food.
en.tip_seating: Sit inside if there is no show that night. The place features a fun bar outside in the summer.
en.tip_parking: Use the south parking lot at the Jaffa port.

en.name: The Salon
en.tip: Order well in advance, it's tricky. Open Wednesdays and Thursdays.
en.tip_dish: There's no set menu really.
en.tip_seating: You'll find it hard to choose a table of your choice.
en.tip_parking: And there's little parking available. But trust us, it's worth it.

en.name: Goocha
en.tip: A fun seafood restaurant at the heart of Tel Aviv.
en.tip_dish: Order mussles and fries.
en.tip_seating: On a nice day you can sit outside on Dizingoff st.
en.tip_parking: Take a taxi.

en.name: Orna & Ella
en.tip: A classy place that is also vegan and gluten friendly.
en.tip_dish: Order the wweet potato latkes.
en.tip_seating: We don't have any special seating recommendation.
en.tip_parking: take a taxi.

en.name: Seatara
en.tip: Located at the northern tip of Tel Aviv, at a seaside complex, it's a great way to end your day.
en.tip_dish: Order at least one of the focaccias.
en.tip_seating: Sit at the window side, or ask for a place outside if the weather is nice.
en.tip_parking: Street parking should be fine, but there's a lot nearby.

en.name: MantaRay
en.tip: A great place for dinner at sunset. Don't miss out.
en.tip_dish: Order the starters out of a mix and match tray.
en.tip_seating: Sit on the outside balcony if it's summer.
en.tip_parking: Use the Alma beach parking lot.

en.name: Rokach 73
en.tip: Located at the north of the City, near the tennis club.
en.tip_seating: No special seating recommendations.
en.tip_parking: There's parking at the location.

en.name: Italkia Baâ€™Tachana
en.tip: A Perfect venue for tourist in the evening.
en.tip_dish: Order the "Bloody" steak.
en.tip_seating: Any table is good.
en.tip_parking: There is plenty of paid parking at the old station complex.

en.name: Hahaluzim 3
en.tip: Great restaurant with a bar feel.
en.tip_dish: Order the open bread cornbeef sandwich.
en.tip_seating: Sit on the bar or the corner table near the entrance.
en.tip_parking: Haluzim st. has plenty of parking.

en.name: Thai House
en.tip: One of few good thai restaurants in TLV.
en.tip_dish: Order the Pahak Bong, spicy and fun.
en.tip_seating: Don't expect a good table.
en.tip_parking: There is paid parking nearby.

en.name: The Diner
en.tip: A Goofy and fun diner at the heart of the city.
en.tip_dish: Have the burger.
en.tip_seating: No special seating recommended here, it's all fun.
en.tip_parking: There is some paid parking nearby on Ibn Gevirol.

en.name: The Six TLV
en.tip: A cafe-restaurant to make you feel like you're in Paris.
en.tip_dish: Honestly the the burger is awsome.
en.tip_seating: Sit outside on the street.
en.tip_parking: There should be enough street parking on Zabotinsky st.

en.name: May 6
en.tip: An ideal for sitting outside with friends. Great food and conveniently close to Dizzingoff fountain.
en.tip_dish: Order all the starters, don't think twice.
en.tip_seating: Sit outside.
en.tip_parking: Taking a taxi to Dizingoff square is probably the best idea.

en.name: Milgo & Milbar
en.tip: A place for a fun evening on Rothschild.
en.tip_dish: Order the fish tartar and beetroot cream.
en.tip_seating: The bar here is a pretty cool place to sit.
en.tip_parking: Use the paid parking at Habima nearby.

en.name: CafÃ© Italia
en.tip: Good old Italian food, happy hour feel.
en.tip_dish: Try the chocolare mousse, it's simply perfect.
en.tip_seating: Sit at the round table on the left side of the restaurant.
en.tip_parking: There is nearby street parking.

en.name: Zuk
en.tip: A deli restaurant at the very north of Tel Aviv.
en.tip_dish: Choose your own meat.
en.tip_seating: Ask for the bar, near the open kitchen.
en.tip_parking: You should be able to find street parking

en.name: Lobi
en.tip: A fun a packed place at the heart of northern Tel Aviv.
en.tip_dish: Order the shpondra tortellini.
en.tip_seating: FYI, it's crowded here.
en.tip_parking: There's an often full paid lot a bit far off. You're better off with a taxi.

en.name: Topolopompo
en.tip: A stylish Asia meat restaurant, as pricey as they come.
en.tip_dish: Order the Ssam Talia
en.tip_seating: Any table is great.
en.tip_parking: There's plenty of street parking around.

en.name: Ten
en.tip: A meat and sea food restaurant with two master chefs for each cuisine.
en.tip_dish: Order the Asado or polenta.
en.tip_seating: No table preferences.
en.tip_parking: A number of parking option a block or two away.

en.name: Zou Bisou
en.tip: A bar with a great food selection, set to the mood of "mad men".
en.tip_dish: Have the ramen noodle bun hamburger.
en.tip_seating: More fun on the bar.
en.tip_parking: No paking around these parts. Take a taxi.

en.name: Yafo Tel-Aviv
en.tip: A more formal occasion would suit this place best.
en.tip_dish: The beef tenderloin or Ossobuco are our recommendations
en.tip_seating: The nicer seats are by the windows.
en.tip_parking: There is ample street parking nearby.

en.name: La Repubblica di Ronimotti
en.tip: A fresh urban Italian restaurant located at an upscale complex close to Rothschild.
en.tip_dish: The pasta dishes are home-made in the kitchen.
en.tip_seating: Avoid sitting too close to the antipasti counters.
en.tip_parking: Use the paid parking at the complex.

en.name: Hudson
en.tip: An excellent meat restaurant in the hi-tech complex at the north of Tel Aviv.
en.tip_dish: Have the hamburger or any of the excellent meat choices.
en.tip_seating: Make sure to sit far from the service area in the hall on the left.
en.tip_parking: Use the paid parking lots on Habarzel or Hanechoshet street.

en.name: Cafe 48
en.tip: A great kitchen serving medium size portions.
en.tip_dish: Have the crack pie for desert.
en.tip_seating: There's an excellent bar, and the rest of the place is also great.
en.tip_parking: There is nearby paid parking.

en.name: Taqueria
en.tip: A mexican place for fun and friends.
en.tip_dish: The nachos are said to be fantastic.
en.tip_seating: No sitting preferences.
en.tip_parking: There's street parking around.

en.name: Basta
en.tip: A local gem at the south of Tel Aviv.
en.tip_dish: It's all jsut so good. But try the "meurav yerushalmi".
en.tip_seating: The bar is very inviting.
en.tip_parking: Come by taxi.

en.name: Cordelia
en.tip: A unique setting in Jaffa.
en.tip_dish: Order the tasting menu.
en.tip_seating: There's also an intimate lounge inside.
en.tip_parking: Take a taxi.

en.name: Shine & Sharp
en.tip: A celebrity meat restaurants at the east of Tel Aviv.
en.tip_dish: Have the bonless chicken wings.
en.tip_seating: We have no seating recomendation.
en.tip_parking: There's ample street parking nearby or a close parking lot.

en.name: Lobi
en.tip: A food bar at the north of Tel Aviv. Young and vibrant.
en.tip_dish: Try the goose liver.
en.tip_seating: It's a pretty tightly packed place to sit, come prepared.
en.tip_parking: There's really litle parking around, one lot which is usually full. Take a taxi.
